.TH COGDEMO 1
.SH NAME
cogdemo \- Plan9Cog demonstration program
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cogdemo
[
.B -a
] [
.B -p
] [
.B -e
] [
.B -s
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Cogdemo
is a demonstration program that showcases the capabilities of Plan9Cog,
the AGI-enabled Plan 9 operating system. It demonstrates AtomSpace operations,
PLN inference, ECAN attention allocation, and system information.
.PP
With no options, all demonstrations are run in sequence. Options select
specific demonstrations:
.TP
.B -a
Run the AtomSpace demonstration showing node and link creation, truth values,
and basic knowledge representation.
.TP
.B -p
Run the PLN (Probabilistic Logic Networks) demonstration showing deduction,
induction, abduction, revision, and boolean operations with uncertain reasoning.
.TP
.B -e
Run the ECAN (Economic Attention Network) demonstration showing attention
allocation, attentional focus, attention spreading, and decay.
.TP
.B -s
Display Plan9Cog system information including version, uptime, atom count,
and memory usage.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run all demonstrations:
.IP
.EX
cogdemo
.EE
.PP
Run only the AtomSpace demo:
.IP
.EX
cogdemo -a
.EE
.PP
Run PLN and ECAN demos:
.IP
.EX
cogdemo -p -e
.EE
.SH FILES
.TF /sys/include/plan9cog.h
.TP
.B /sys/include/plan9cog.h
Plan9Cog main header
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/cogdemo
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR cogctl (1),
.IR cogfs (4),
.IR plan9cog (2)
.SH BUGS
None known.
